<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>AI-102 Exam Prep</title>
<script>
// ==================== EXAM CONFIG ====================
// To clone this app for another exam, update ONLY this block.
// Everything else adapts automatically.
const EXAM_CONFIG = {
  id: 'ai102',                          // localStorage prefix + URL slug
  code: 'AI-102',                        // Display code
  name: 'Designing and Implementing a Microsoft Azure AI Solution',
  url: 'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/azure-ai-engineer/',
  examDate: null,                        // Set to 'YYYY-MM-DD' to show countdown, or null to hide
  passingScore: 700,                     // Microsoft passing score (out of 1000)
  ghPages: 'https://demo-ninjas.github.io/pass_ai_102/'
};
</script>
<style>
:root {
  --bg: #0f172a; --surface: #1e293b; --surface2: #334155;
  --accent: #3b82f6; --accent2: #8b5cf6; --green: #22c55e; --red: #ef4444; --orange: #f59e0b;
  --text: #f1f5f9; --text2: #94a3b8; --text3: #64748b;
  --radius: 12px; --shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.3);
}
* { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
body { font-family: 'Segoe UI',system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif; background:var(--bg); color:var(--text); min-height:100vh; }
button { cursor:pointer; font-family:inherit; border:none; }
a { color:var(--accent); }

/* Header */
.header { background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e3a5f,#2d1b69); padding:20px 24px; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid var(--surface2); }
.header h1 { font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:4px; }
.header .countdown { color:var(--orange); font-size:.95rem; font-weight:600; margin-top:6px; }
.header .countdown.passed { color:var(--green); }
.header .subtitle { color:var(--text2); font-size:.85rem; margin-top:4px; }
.header .subtitle a { color:var(--text2); text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:2px; }
.header .subtitle a:hover { color:var(--accent); }

/* Nav */
.nav { display:flex; background:var(--surface); border-bottom:1px solid var(--surface2); overflow-x:auto; }
.nav button { flex:1; min-width:0; padding:14px 8px; background:transparent; color:var(--text2); font-size:.85rem; font-weight:600; border-bottom:3px solid transparent; transition:all .2s; white-space:nowrap; }
.nav button.active { color:var(--accent); border-bottom-color:var(--accent); background:rgba(59,130,246,.08); }
.nav button:hover:not(.active) { color:var(--text); background:rgba(255,255,255,.03); }
.nav .badge { display:inline-block; background:var(--accent); color:#fff; font-size:.7rem; padding:1px 6px; border-radius:99px; margin-left:4px; vertical-align:middle; }

/* Panels */
.panel { display:none; padding:20px; max-width:800px; margin:0 auto; }
.panel.active { display:block; }

/* Cards */
.card { background:var(--surface); border-radius:var(--radius); padding:24px; margin-bottom:16px; box-shadow:var(--shadow); }

/* Flashcard */
.fc-container { perspective:1000px; margin:20px auto; max-width:600px; }
.fc-card { position:relative; width:100%; min-height:260px; transition:transform .5s; transform-style:preserve-3d; cursor:pointer; }
.fc-card.flipped { transform:rotateY(180deg); }
.fc-face { position:absolute; inset:0; backface-visibility:hidden; border-radius:var(--radius); padding:32px 24px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; justify-content:center; align-items:center; text-align:center; }
.fc-front { background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e3a5f,#1e293b); border:1px solid var(--surface2); }
.fc-back { background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1a4731,#1e293b); border:1px solid #22c55e33; transform:rotateY(180deg); }
.fc-domain { font-size:.75rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1px; margin-bottom:12px; }
.fc-question { font-size:1.15rem; line-height:1.5; }
.fc-answer { font-size:1.15rem; line-height:1.5; color:var(--green); font-weight:600; }
.fc-hint { font-size:.8rem; color:var(--text3); margin-top:16px; }
.fc-actions { display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:center; margin-top:20px; }
.fc-actions button { padding:12px 28px; border-radius:99px; font-weight:600; font-size:.9rem; transition:all .2s; }
.btn-wrong { background:rgba(239,68,68,.15); color:var(--red); border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,.3); }
.btn-wrong:hover { background:rgba(239,68,68,.25); }
.btn-right { background:rgba(34,197,94,.15); color:var(--green); border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,.3); }
.btn-right:hover { background:rgba(34,197,94,.25); }
.fc-progress { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:16px; color:var(--text2); font-size:.85rem; }
.fc-progress .bar { flex:1; height:6px; background:var(--surface2); border-radius:99px; overflow:hidden; }
.fc-progress .bar-fill { height:100%; background:var(--accent); border-radius:99px; transition:width .3s; }
.fc-filters { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:16px; justify-content:center; }
.fc-filters button { padding:6px 14px; border-radius:99px; font-size:.78rem; font-weight:600; background:var(--surface2); color:var(--text2); transition:all .2s; }
.fc-filters button.active { background:var(--accent); color:#fff; }

/* Quiz */
.quiz-q { font-size:1.1rem; line-height:1.5; margin-bottom:20px; }
.quiz-opts label { display:block; padding:14px 18px; margin-bottom:8px; background:var(--surface2); border-radius:var(--radius); cursor:pointer; transition:all .2s; border:2px solid transparent; font-size:.95rem; }
.quiz-opts label:hover { background:#3b4d63; }
.quiz-opts label.selected { border-color:var(--accent); background:rgba(59,130,246,.1); }
.quiz-opts label.correct { border-color:var(--green); background:rgba(34,197,94,.1); }
.quiz-opts label.wrong { border-color:var(--red); background:rgba(239,68,68,.1); }
.quiz-opts input { display:none; }
.quiz-explanation { margin-top:16px; padding:16px; background:rgba(34,197,94,.08); border-radius:var(--radius); border-left:3px solid var(--green); font-size:.9rem; line-height:1.5; }
.quiz-score { text-align:center; padding:32px; }
.quiz-score .big { font-size:3rem; font-weight:800; }
.quiz-score .pct { font-size:1.2rem; color:var(--text2); margin-top:8px; }

/* Progress */
.progress-domain { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:14px; }
.progress-domain .label { width:140px; font-size:.85rem; font-weight:600; flex-shrink:0; }
.progress-domain .bar { flex:1; height:24px; background:var(--surface2); border-radius:var(--radius); overflow:hidden; position:relative; }
.progress-domain .bar-fill { height:100%; border-radius:var(--radius); transition:width .5s; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:flex-end; padding-right:8px; font-size:.75rem; font-weight:700; min-width:fit-content; }
.stats-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr)); gap:12px; margin-bottom:24px; }
.stat-card { background:var(--surface); border-radius:var(--radius); padding:20px; text-align:center; }
.stat-card .num { font-size:2rem; font-weight:800; }
.stat-card .lbl { font-size:.8rem; color:var(--text2); margin-top:4px; }

/* Cheat Sheet */
.cs-section { border:1px solid var(--surface2); border-radius:var(--radius); margin-bottom:8px; overflow:hidden; }
.cs-header { padding:14px 18px; background:var(--surface); cursor:pointer; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; font-weight:600; font-size:.95rem; transition:background .2s; }
.cs-header:hover { background:var(--surface2); }
.cs-header .arrow { transition:transform .2s; color:var(--text3); }
.cs-section.open .arrow { transform:rotate(90deg); }
.cs-body { padding:0 18px; max-height:0; overflow:hidden; transition:max-height .3s ease, padding .3s; }
.cs-section.open .cs-body { max-height:5000px; padding:16px 18px; }

/* Mind Maps */
.mm-section { border:1px solid var(--surface2); border-radius:var(--radius); margin-bottom:12px; overflow:hidden; }
.mm-header { padding:16px 18px; background:var(--surface); cursor:pointer; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; font-weight:600; font-size:1rem; transition:background .2s; }
.mm-header:hover { background:var(--surface2); }
.mm-header .arrow { transition:transform .3s; color:var(--text3); font-size:.9rem; }
.mm-section.open .arrow { transform:rotate(90deg); }
.mm-body { max-height:0; overflow:hidden; transition:max-height .4s ease; }
.mm-section.open .mm-body { max-height:5000px; }
.mm-wrap { height:75vh; min-height:600px; background:var(--bg); border-top:1px solid var(--surface2); position:relative; }
.mm-wrap svg { width:100%; height:100%; }
.mm-wrap svg text { font-size:16px !important; fill:#e2e8f0 !important; }
.mm-wrap svg foreignObject { font-size:15px !important; color:#e2e8f0 !important; }
.mm-wrap svg path { stroke-opacity:.6 !important; }
.mm-wrap svg circle { fill:var(--bg) !important; stroke-width:2px !important; }
.mm-fullscreen-btn { position:absolute; top:10px; right:10px; z-index:10; background:var(--surface2); border:1px solid var(--surface2); color:var(--text1); padding:6px 12px; border-radius:6px; cursor:pointer; font-size:.85rem; opacity:.7; transition:opacity .2s; }
.mm-fullscreen-btn:hover { opacity:1; }
.mm-wrap.mm-expanded { position:fixed; top:0; left:0; width:100vw; height:100vh; z-index:9999; min-height:unset; border-radius:0; border:none; }
.mm-wrap.mm-expanded .mm-fullscreen-btn { top:16px; right:16px; }
.cs-table { width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:.85rem; }
.cs-table th { text-align:left; padding:8px; border-bottom:2px solid var(--surface2); color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; }
.cs-table td { padding:8px; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.05); }
.cs-table code { background:var(--surface2); padding:2px 6px; border-radius:4px; font-size:.82rem; }

/* Buttons */
.btn { padding:12px 24px; border-radius:var(--radius); font-weight:600; font-size:.9rem; transition:all .2s; }
.btn-primary { background:var(--accent); color:#fff; }
.btn-primary:hover { background:#2563eb; }
.btn-secondary { background:var(--surface2); color:var(--text); }
.btn-secondary:hover { background:#475569; }
.btn-sm { padding:8px 16px; font-size:.82rem; }

/* Utils */
.text-center { text-align:center; }
.mt-12 { margin-top:12px; }
.mt-20 { margin-top:20px; }
.mb-16 { margin-bottom:16px; }
.flex-center { display:flex; justify-content:center; gap:12px; }
.tag { display:inline-block; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:99px; font-size:.75rem; font-weight:600; }
.tag-blue { background:rgba(59,130,246,.15); color:var(--accent); }
.tag-green { background:rgba(34,197,94,.15); color:var(--green); }
.tag-red { background:rgba(239,68,68,.15); color:var(--red); }
.tag-orange { background:rgba(245,158,11,.15); color:var(--orange); }

@media(max-width:600px){
  .fc-face { padding:24px 16px; }
  .fc-question, .fc-answer { font-size:1rem; }
  .fc-filters { gap:6px; }
  .fc-filters button { padding:5px 10px; font-size:.72rem; }
  .fc-actions button { padding:10px 20px; font-size:.85rem; }
  .progress-domain { flex-direction:column; align-items:stretch; }
  .progress-domain .label { width:auto; }
  .stats-grid { grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr); }
  .nav { gap:0; }
  .nav button { font-size:.72rem; padding:10px 2px; letter-spacing:-.3px; }
  .panel { padding:14px; }
  .card { padding:16px; }
  .quiz-q { font-size:1rem; }
  .quiz-opts label { padding:12px 14px; font-size:.88rem; }
  .mm-wrap { height:60vh; min-height:400px; }
  .cs-header { padding:12px 14px; font-size:.88rem; }
  .cs-body { padding:0 12px; }
  .cs-section.open .cs-body { padding:12px; }
  .cs-table { font-size:.78rem; }
  .header h1 { font-size:1.3rem; }
  .btn { padding:10px 18px; font-size:.85rem; }
}
@media(max-width:375px){
  .nav button { font-size:.68rem; padding:8px 1px; }
  .fc-filters button { padding:4px 8px; font-size:.68rem; }
  .stats-grid { grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:8px; }
  .stat-card { padding:14px; }
  .stat-card .num { font-size:1.6rem; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="header" id="app-header">
  <h1 id="header-title">🎯 AI-102 Exam Prep</h1>
  <div class="subtitle" id="header-subtitle">Designing and Implementing a Microsoft Azure AI Solution</div>
  <div class="countdown" id="header-countdown" style="display:none"></div>
</div>
<script>
// Dynamic header from config
(function(){
  document.getElementById('header-title').textContent = '🎯 ' + EXAM_CONFIG.code + ' Exam Prep';
  document.title = EXAM_CONFIG.code + ' Exam Prep';
  document.getElementById('header-subtitle').innerHTML = `<a href="${EXAM_CONFIG.url}" target="_blank">${EXAM_CONFIG.name}</a>`;
  if(EXAM_CONFIG.examDate){
    const cd = document.getElementById('header-countdown');
    const exam = new Date(EXAM_CONFIG.examDate + 'T00:00:00');
    const now = new Date(); now.setHours(0,0,0,0);
    const days = Math.ceil((exam - now) / 86400000);
    cd.style.display = '';
    if(days > 0){ cd.textContent = `⏰ ${days} day${days!==1?'s':''} until exam`; }
    else if(days === 0){ cd.textContent = '🔥 Exam day — you got this!'; cd.classList.add('passed'); }
    else { cd.textContent = '✅ Exam date passed'; cd.classList.add('passed'); }
  }
})();
</script>

<div class="nav" id="nav">
  <button data-tab="flashcards" class="active">🃏 Flashcards</button>
  <button data-tab="quiz">📝 Quiz</button>
  <button data-tab="mindmaps">🧠 Mind Maps</button>
  <button data-tab="progress">📊 Progress</button>
  <button data-tab="cheatsheets">📋 Cheat Sheets</button>
</div>

<!-- FLASHCARDS -->
<div class="panel active" id="tab-flashcards">
  <div class="fc-filters" id="fc-filters"></div>
  <div class="fc-progress">
    <span id="fc-count">0/0</span>
    <div class="bar"><div class="bar-fill" id="fc-bar" style="width:0%"></div></div>
    <span id="fc-pct">0%</span>
  </div>
  <div class="fc-container">
    <div class="fc-card" id="fc-card" onclick="flipCard()">
      <div class="fc-face fc-front">
        <div class="fc-domain" id="fc-domain"></div>
        <div class="fc-question" id="fc-question"></div>
        <div class="fc-hint">Click to reveal answer</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fc-face fc-back">
        <div class="fc-domain">Answer</div>
        <div class="fc-answer" id="fc-answer"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="fc-actions" id="fc-actions" style="display:none">
    <button class="btn-wrong" onclick="markCard(false)">✗ Again</button>
    <button class="btn-right" onclick="markCard(true)">✓ Got it</button>
  </div>
  <div class="text-center mt-20" id="fc-done" style="display:none">
    <div style="font-size:2.5rem; margin-bottom:12px;">🎉</div>
    <h2>Deck Complete!</h2>
    <p class="mt-12" style="color:var(--text2)" id="fc-summary"></p>
    <div class="flex-center mt-20">
      <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="resetDeck()">Start Over</button>
      <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="reviewStarred()">Review ★ Starred</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- QUIZ -->
<div class="panel" id="tab-quiz">
  <div id="quiz-setup">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:16px;">Practice Quiz</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text2); margin-bottom:20px;">Test yourself with scenario-based multiple choice questions. Select a domain or take a mixed quiz.</p>
      <div class="fc-filters" id="quiz-domain-filters"></div>
      <div class="flex-center mt-20">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="startQuiz(10)">10 Questions</button>
        <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="startQuiz(25)">25 Questions</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="quiz-active" style="display:none">
    <div class="fc-progress">
      <span id="quiz-count">0/0</span>
      <div class="bar"><div class="bar-fill" id="quiz-bar" style="width:0%"></div></div>
      <span id="quiz-score-live">0 correct</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="fc-domain" id="quiz-domain"></div>
      <div class="quiz-q" id="quiz-question"></div>
      <div class="quiz-opts" id="quiz-opts"></div>
      <div class="quiz-explanation" id="quiz-explanation" style="display:none"></div>
      <div class="flex-center mt-20">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" id="quiz-next" style="display:none" onclick="nextQuizQ()">Next →</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="quiz-results" style="display:none">
    <div class="card quiz-score">
      <div class="big" id="quiz-final-score"></div>
      <div class="pct" id="quiz-final-pct"></div>
      <div class="mt-20" id="quiz-pass-msg"></div>
      <div class="flex-center mt-20">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="resetQuiz()">Try Again</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="quiz-review"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MIND MAPS -->
<div class="panel" id="tab-mindmaps">
  <div class="card mb-16" style="text-align:center;padding:16px">
    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:.9rem">💡 Click a domain to expand its mind map. Scroll to zoom, drag to pan.</p>
  </div>
  <div id="mm-container"></div>
</div>

<!-- PROGRESS -->
<div class="panel" id="tab-progress">
  <div class="stats-grid" id="stats-grid"></div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;">Flashcard Mastery by Domain</h3>
    <div id="progress-bars"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="card mt-20">
    <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;">Study Streak</h3>
    <div id="streak-info"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex-center mt-20">
    <button class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" onclick="resetAllProgress()">Reset All Progress</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- CHEAT SHEETS -->
<div class="panel" id="tab-cheatsheets">
  <div class="fc-filters mb-16" id="cs-filters"></div>
  <div id="cs-content"></div>
</div>

<script>
// ==================== DATA ====================
const DOMAINS = [
  { id:'d1', name:'Plan & Manage', weight:'20-25%', color:'#3b82f6' },
  { id:'d2', name:'Generative AI', weight:'15-20%', color:'#8b5cf6' },
  { id:'d3', name:'Agentic', weight:'5-10%', color:'#06b6d4' },
  { id:'d4', name:'Computer Vision', weight:'10-15%', color:'#f59e0b' },
  { id:'d5', name:'NLP & Speech', weight:'15-20%', color:'#22c55e' },
  { id:'d6', name:'Knowledge Mining', weight:'15-20%', color:'#ef4444' }
];

const FLASHCARDS = [
  // Domain 1
  {id:1,d:'d1',q:'You need Azure AI Language AND Vision with one key. What resource type?',a:'Multi-service resource'},
  {id:2,d:'d1',q:'You need separate billing per AI service. What resource type?',a:'Single-service resource'},
  {id:3,d:'d1',q:'Which resource type offers a free tier (F0)?',a:'Single-service only'},
  {id:4,d:'d1',q:'What header passes a subscription key to Azure AI APIs?',a:'Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key'},
  {id:5,d:'d1',q:'What header passes an Entra ID token?',a:'Authorization: Bearer <token>'},
  {id:6,d:'d1',q:'What SDK class auto-handles Entra ID, managed identity, CLI creds?',a:'DefaultAzureCredential'},
  {id:7,d:'d1',q:'Key rotation order for zero downtime?',a:'App uses Key1 → regen Key2 → switch to Key2 → regen Key1'},
  {id:8,d:'d1',q:'Where should you store Azure AI keys in production?',a:'Azure Key Vault'},
  {id:9,d:'d1',q:'RBAC role to call APIs but NOT manage resources?',a:'Cognitive Services User'},
  {id:10,d:'d1',q:'RBAC role to manage AND call Azure OpenAI?',a:'Cognitive Services OpenAI Contributor'},
  {id:11,d:'d1',q:'Private Endpoint vs Service Endpoint?',a:'Private Endpoint = private IP in VNet. Service Endpoint = optimized route, still public IP.'},
  {id:12,d:'d1',q:'Do Azure AI containers need internet?',a:'Yes for billing (phone-home), unless disconnected container (special approval)'},
  {id:13,d:'d1',q:'Deployment type guaranteeing min tokens/minute?',a:'Provisioned Throughput (PTU)'},
  {id:14,d:'d1',q:'Name Microsoft\'s 6 Responsible AI principles.',a:'Fairness, Reliability & Safety, Privacy & Security, Inclusiveness, Transparency, Accountability'},
  {id:15,d:'d1',q:'What blocks SPECIFIC TERMS you define in Azure OpenAI?',a:'Blocklist (not content filter — that\'s category-based)'},
  {id:16,d:'d1',q:'What detects prompt injection / jailbreak?',a:'Prompt shields'},
  {id:17,d:'d1',q:'What checks if response is supported by context?',a:'Groundedness detection'},
  {id:18,d:'d1',q:'Content filters apply to input only, output only, or both?',a:'BOTH input (prompt) AND output (completion)'},
  {id:19,d:'d1',q:'Name the 4 content filter categories.',a:'Hate, Sexual, Violence, Self-harm'},
  {id:20,d:'d1',q:'Azure Translator uses what unique endpoint?',a:'api.cognitive.microsofttranslator.com (global, NOT resource-specific)'},
  {id:21,d:'d1',q:'What extra header does Translator require?',a:'Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Region'},
  // Domain 2
  {id:22,d:'d2',q:'What parameter controls randomness? Range?',a:'temperature, 0.0–2.0'},
  {id:23,d:'d2',q:'What parameter does nucleus sampling? Range?',a:'top_p, 0.0–1.0'},
  {id:24,d:'d2',q:'Should you set both temperature AND top_p?',a:'No — modify one, leave the other at default'},
  {id:25,d:'d2',q:'Low temperature (0.0-0.3) is best for?',a:'Deterministic, factual: code gen, data extraction'},
  {id:26,d:'d2',q:'What reduces word repetition based on frequency?',a:'frequency_penalty (-2.0 to 2.0)'},
  {id:27,d:'d2',q:'What encourages new topics?',a:'presence_penalty (-2.0 to 2.0)'},
  {id:28,d:'d2',q:'Max stop sequences?',a:'4'},
  {id:29,d:'d2',q:'Message role that defines AI behavior/persona?',a:'system'},
  {id:30,d:'d2',q:'Message role used for few-shot examples?',a:'assistant (paired with user messages)'},
  {id:31,d:'d2',q:'RAG pattern in one sentence?',a:'Query → Search retrieves docs → docs as context → LLM generates grounded answer'},
  {id:32,d:'d2',q:'In RAG, what converts text to vectors?',a:'Embedding model (text-embedding-3-small/large)'},
  {id:33,d:'d2',q:'GPT-4o context: input? output?',a:'128K input / 16K output'},
  {id:34,d:'d2',q:'Foundry: top-level shared resource?',a:'Hub'},
  {id:35,d:'d2',q:'Foundry: isolated workspace within a hub?',a:'Project'},
  {id:36,d:'d2',q:'Foundry tool for visual LLM orchestration?',a:'Prompt flow'},
  {id:37,d:'d2',q:'Name 4 Foundry evaluation metrics.',a:'Groundedness, Relevance, Coherence, Fluency'},
  {id:38,d:'d2',q:'Fine-tuning vs RAG: when use which?',a:'RAG for dynamic data grounding. Fine-tuning for style/format/domain behavior.'},
  {id:39,d:'d2',q:'Fine-tuning minimum examples?',a:'10 (50-100+ recommended)'},
  {id:40,d:'d2',q:'Fine-tuning data format?',a:'JSONL with {"messages": [...]} per line'},
  // Domain 3
  {id:41,d:'d3',q:'Agent vs chatbot: key difference?',a:'Agent plans, uses tools, iterates autonomously. Chatbot just responds.'},
  {id:42,d:'d3',q:'Name 3 Foundry Agent Service built-in tools.',a:'Code Interpreter, File Search, Function Calling'},
  {id:43,d:'d3',q:'Agent API object that holds conversation?',a:'Thread'},
  {id:44,d:'d3',q:'Agent API object that triggers processing?',a:'Run'},
  {id:45,d:'d3',q:'Name 3 multi-agent orchestration patterns.',a:'Sequential, Parallel, Hierarchical, Collaborative'},
  {id:46,d:'d3',q:'Semantic Kernel: what auto-creates plans?',a:'Planner'},
  {id:141,d:'d3',q:'What is the Agent Service API flow (5 steps)?',a:'Create Agent → Create Thread → Add Messages → Create Run → Poll results'},
  {id:142,d:'d3',q:'Agent built-in tool that executes Python in a sandbox?',a:'Code Interpreter'},
  {id:143,d:'d3',q:'Agent tool that searches uploaded files with vectors?',a:'File Search'},
  {id:144,d:'d3',q:'Semantic Kernel: what is a Kernel?',a:'Central orchestrator that holds services, plugins, and memory'},
  {id:145,d:'d3',q:'Semantic Kernel: what links to AI services like OpenAI?',a:'Connector'},
  {id:146,d:'d3',q:'Human-in-the-loop in multi-agent means?',a:'Involving a human for approval at key decision points'},
  // Domain 4
  {id:47,d:'d4',q:'Name all 7 Image Analysis 4.0 features.',a:'caption, denseCaptions, tags, objects, people, smartCrops, read'},
  {id:48,d:'d4',q:'Face detection model best for blurry faces?',a:'detection_02 (or detection_03 for best overall)'},
  {id:49,d:'d4',q:'Which detection model returns NO landmarks?',a:'detection_02'},
  {id:50,d:'d4',q:'Best overall face detection model?',a:'detection_03'},
  {id:51,d:'d4',q:'Best face recognition model? Special feature?',a:'recognition_04 — works with face masks'},
  {id:52,d:'d4',q:'Default detection model if unspecified?',a:'detection_01'},
  {id:53,d:'d4',q:'Default recognition model if unspecified?',a:'recognition_01'},
  {id:54,d:'d4',q:'Can you change a PersonGroup\'s recognition model?',a:'No — immutable once created'},
  {id:55,d:'d4',q:'QualityForRecognition: what level for enrollment?',a:'High'},
  {id:56,d:'d4',q:'Face ID time-to-live default?',a:'86400 seconds (24 hours)'},
  {id:57,d:'d4',q:'Custom Vision classification min images/tag?',a:'5 (30+ recommended)'},
  {id:58,d:'d4',q:'Custom Vision object detection min images/tag?',a:'15 (50+ recommended)'},
  {id:59,d:'d4',q:'Precision measures what?',a:'Of predicted positives, how many are correct'},
  {id:60,d:'d4',q:'Recall measures what?',a:'Of actual positives, how many were found'},
  {id:61,d:'d4',q:'High precision + low recall means?',a:'Rarely wrong when it says "yes", but misses many actual positives'},
  {id:62,d:'d4',q:'Spatial Analysis runs on what?',a:'Edge devices (Docker container, NVIDIA GPU, RTSP video)'},
  {id:63,d:'d4',q:'Minimum detectable face size?',a:'36 × 36 pixels'},
  // Domain 5
  {id:64,d:'d5',q:'Sentiment analysis possible values?',a:'positive, negative, neutral, mixed'},
  {id:65,d:'d5',q:'Key phrase extraction: confidence scores?',a:'No — just strings'},
  {id:66,d:'d5',q:'What links entities to Wikipedia?',a:'Entity Linking'},
  {id:67,d:'d5',q:'PII detection replaces entities with?',a:'***** (asterisks) in redactedText'},
  {id:68,d:'d5',q:'Language detection: need language field in request?',a:'No — it auto-detects'},
  {id:69,d:'d5',q:'Max document size for Text Analytics?',a:'5,120 characters'},
  {id:70,d:'d5',q:'Translator: translate to multiple languages in one call?',a:'Yes — to=fr&to=de&to=ja'},
  {id:71,d:'d5',q:'SSML tag for rate, pitch, volume?',a:'<prosody>'},
  {id:72,d:'d5',q:'SSML tag for a pause?',a:'<break time="500ms"/>'},
  {id:73,d:'d5',q:'SSML tag for emotional style?',a:'<mstts:express-as style="cheerful">'},
  {id:74,d:'d5',q:'SDK class for speech + intent recognition?',a:'IntentRecognizer (not SpeechRecognizer)'},
  {id:75,d:'d5',q:'SDK class for speech translation?',a:'TranslationRecognizer'},
  {id:76,d:'d5',q:'CLU: what is an "intent"?',a:'What the user wants to do (e.g., BookFlight)'},
  {id:77,d:'d5',q:'Name the 4 CLU entity types.',a:'Learned, List, Prebuilt, Regex'},
  {id:78,d:'d5',q:'What CLU intent must you always include?',a:'None intent (catches out-of-scope)'},
  {id:79,d:'d5',q:'Question Answering: what\'s multi-turn?',a:'Follow-up prompts to drill deeper'},
  {id:80,d:'d5',q:'Custom Translator min parallel sentences?',a:'10,000+ for good quality'},
  // Domain 6
  {id:81,d:'d6',q:'Name 5 Azure AI Search core components.',a:'Data source, Indexer, Skillset, Index, Knowledge Store'},
  {id:82,d:'d6',q:'fieldMappings vs outputFieldMappings?',a:'fieldMappings = before enrichment. outputFieldMappings = after skillset.'},
  {id:83,d:'d6',q:'Custom skill implemented as what?',a:'Azure Function (HTTP trigger, Web API skill)'},
  {id:84,d:'d6',q:'Custom skill response must include what 3 fields?',a:'data, errors, warnings'},
  {id:85,d:'d6',q:'Field attribute needed for $filter?',a:'filterable'},
  {id:86,d:'d6',q:'Field attribute needed for $orderby?',a:'sortable'},
  {id:87,d:'d6',q:'Simple query: space = OR or AND?',a:'OR'},
  {id:88,d:'d6',q:'Enable full Lucene syntax how?',a:'queryType=full'},
  {id:89,d:'d6',q:'searchMode=all vs any?',a:'all = AND, any = OR (default)'},
  {id:90,d:'d6',q:'Name the 4 scoring profile function types.',a:'magnitude, freshness, distance, tag'},
  {id:91,d:'d6',q:'Suggester searchMode value?',a:'analyzingInfixMatching'},
  {id:92,d:'d6',q:'Knowledge store table projections → stored where?',a:'Azure Table Storage'},
  {id:93,d:'d6',q:'What skill reshapes data for projections?',a:'Shaper skill'},
  {id:94,d:'d6',q:'HNSW vs Exhaustive KNN?',a:'HNSW = fast approximate. Exhaustive KNN = slow exact, 100% recall.'},
  {id:95,d:'d6',q:'Best vector metric for text embeddings?',a:'cosine'},
  {id:96,d:'d6',q:'Prebuilt invoice model ID?',a:'prebuilt-invoice'},
  {id:97,d:'d6',q:'Min training docs for custom Doc Intelligence?',a:'5 labeled documents'},
  {id:98,d:'d6',q:'Composed model in Doc Intelligence?',a:'Combines custom models; auto-routes to correct sub-model'},
  {id:99,d:'d6',q:'Semantic search provides what 2 extras?',a:'Semantic captions and semantic answers'},
  {id:100,d:'d6',q:'How does hybrid search merge results?',a:'Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF)'},
  // Missing cards from flashcards.md
  {id:101,d:'d1',q:'Content filter severity levels in order?',a:'safe → low → medium → high'},
  {id:102,d:'d1',q:'What detects copyrighted text/code in AI output?',a:'Protected material detection'},
  {id:103,d:'d1',q:'Name the 4 Azure OpenAI deployment types.',a:'Standard, Global Standard, Provisioned Throughput (PTU), Data Zone Standard'},
  {id:104,d:'d1',q:'Multi-service endpoint URL pattern?',a:'<name>.cognitiveservices.azure.com'},
  {id:105,d:'d1',q:'Azure OpenAI endpoint URL pattern?',a:'<resource>.openai.azure.com/openai/deployments/<deployment>/...'},
  {id:106,d:'d1',q:'Container images come from what registry?',a:'mcr.microsoft.com/azure-cognitive-services/'},
  {id:107,d:'d1',q:'Free tier label?',a:'F0 (Standard = S0)'},
  {id:108,d:'d2',q:'High temperature (0.7-1.5) best for?',a:'Creative: marketing copy, stories, brainstorming'},
  {id:109,d:'d2',q:'Azure OpenAI "On your data" feature does what?',a:'Quick RAG setup — connects to AI Search, no code required'},
  {id:110,d:'d2',q:'Prompt flow node types?',a:'LLM, Python, Prompt, Tool'},
  {id:111,d:'d2',q:'Name prompt engineering techniques.',a:'Zero-shot, Few-shot, Chain-of-thought, Grounding'},
  {id:112,d:'d2',q:'Embedding model dimensions: ada-002 vs 3-large?',a:'ada-002 = 1,536. text-embedding-3-large = 3,072'},
  {id:113,d:'d3',q:'Semantic Kernel: what is a Plugin?',a:'Collection of functions the agent can call'},
  {id:114,d:'d3',q:'Agent Service API flow (5 steps)?',a:'Create Agent → Create Thread → Add Messages → Create Run → Poll results'},
  {id:115,d:'d4',q:'Face API: what does Verify do?',a:'Check if two faces are the same person (1:1 comparison)'},
  {id:116,d:'d4',q:'Face API: what does Identify do?',a:'Match face against a PersonGroup (1:many)'},
  {id:117,d:'d4',q:'Face API: PersonGroup workflow?',a:'Create group → Add persons → Add faces → Train → Identify'},
  {id:118,d:'d4',q:'Custom Vision compact models can be exported to?',a:'ONNX, TensorFlow, CoreML (for mobile/edge)'},
  {id:119,d:'d4',q:'Video Indexer extracts what insights?',a:'Faces, OCR, topics, keywords, sentiment, scenes, transcript, brands'},
  {id:120,d:'d4',q:'Spatial Analysis operations?',a:'Person count, distance, zone crossing, line crossing, dwell time'},
  {id:121,d:'d4',q:'Face max image size?',a:'6 MB'},
  {id:122,d:'d5',q:'SDK class for speech-to-text?',a:'SpeechRecognizer'},
  {id:123,d:'d5',q:'SDK class for text-to-speech?',a:'SpeechSynthesizer'},
  {id:124,d:'d5',q:'SSML: what tag for pronunciation hint (e.g., read "12/25" as date)?',a:'<say-as interpret-as="date">'},
  {id:125,d:'d5',q:'SSML: what tag substitutes text (e.g., "UN" → "United Nations")?',a:'<sub alias="United Nations">'},
  {id:126,d:'d5',q:'Name chit-chat personality options.',a:'Professional, Friendly, Witty, Caring, Enthusiastic'},
  {id:127,d:'d5',q:'What is transliteration?',a:'Converting script (e.g., kanji → romaji), NOT translating meaning'},
  {id:128,d:'d6',q:'@odata.type for a custom Web API skill?',a:'#Microsoft.Skills.Custom.WebApiSkill'},
  {id:129,d:'d6',q:'Context path for extracted images?',a:'/document/normalized_images/*'},
  {id:130,d:'d6',q:'Which interpolations NOT allowed for tag scoring?',a:'quadratic and logarithmic'},
  {id:131,d:'d6',q:'Knowledge store object projections → stored where?',a:'Azure Blob Storage (as JSON)'},
  {id:132,d:'d6',q:'Template model vs Neural model (Doc Intelligence)?',a:'Template = fixed layout. Neural = variable layout.'},
  {id:133,d:'d6',q:'Name 5 built-in AI Search skills.',a:'OCR, Key Phrase Extraction, Entity Recognition, Sentiment, Language Detection'},
  {id:134,d:'d6',q:'Max composed model components?',a:'200'},
  {id:135,d:'d6',q:'AI Search free tier limits?',a:'50 MB storage, 3 indexes'},
  {id:136,d:'d6',q:'Field attribute for faceted navigation?',a:'facetable'},
  {id:147,d:'d6',q:'You want a sidebar showing "Category: Hotels (42), Restaurants (18)". What attribute?',a:'facetable — enables count-by-category navigation'},
  {id:148,d:'d6',q:'You need $filter=rating ge 4. What attribute must the rating field have?',a:'filterable'},
  {id:149,d:'d6',q:'You want users to sort results by price. What attribute on the price field?',a:'sortable'},
  {id:150,d:'d6',q:'A field should be searchable by free text but NOT appear in results. What attributes?',a:'searchable=true, retrievable=false'},
  {id:137,d:'d6',q:'Vector search algorithm types?',a:'HNSW (approximate, default) and Exhaustive KNN (exact, brute force)'},
  {id:138,d:'d6',q:'Semantic config prioritizedFields includes?',a:'titleField, prioritizedContentFields, prioritizedKeywordsFields'},
  {id:139,d:'d4',q:'Image Analysis 4.0: gender-neutral-caption option does what?',a:'Replaces "man/woman" with "person", "boy/girl" with "child"'},
  {id:140,d:'d4',q:'Smart crops aspect ratio range?',a:'0.75 – 1.8'},
  // === DECISION SCENARIO CARDS ===
  // When to choose A vs B
  {id:151,d:'d1',q:'Multi-service vs single-service resource: when use single?',a:'Separate cost tracking per service, need free tier (F0), or different regions per service'},
  {id:152,d:'d1',q:'When to deploy Azure AI as a container instead of cloud?',a:'On-premises/edge, network isolation, low latency, regulatory/data residency requirements'},
  {id:153,d:'d1',q:'Connected container vs disconnected container?',a:'Connected = needs periodic billing phone-home. Disconnected = fully offline (special approval required).'},
  {id:154,d:'d2',q:'RAG vs fine-tuning vs prompt engineering: when use each?',a:'Prompt engineering = first try. RAG = ground in dynamic data. Fine-tuning = teach style/format/domain behavior.'},
  {id:155,d:'d2',q:'When to use semantic search vs vector search vs hybrid?',a:'Semantic = re-rank text results with deep learning. Vector = similarity with embeddings. Hybrid = combine both for best results.'},
  {id:156,d:'d6',q:'Simple query vs Full Lucene: when do you NEED Full Lucene?',a:'When using fuzzy (~), wildcards (*?), field-scoped (field:value), regex, or term boosting (^).'},
  {id:157,d:'d6',q:'Template model vs Neural model in Doc Intelligence?',a:'Template = fixed/identical layouts (same form every time). Neural = variable layouts (different vendors/formats).'},
  {id:158,d:'d4',q:'Classification vs Object Detection in Custom Vision?',a:'Classification = "What is this?" (tag per image). Object Detection = "Where is this?" (tag + bounding box).'},
  {id:159,d:'d6',q:'Prebuilt vs Custom model in Doc Intelligence: when use prebuilt?',a:'When a prebuilt covers your form type (invoice, receipt, ID). Use custom only when prebuilt doesn\'t extract what you need.'},
  {id:160,d:'d5',q:'CLU vs Custom Question Answering: when use which?',a:'CLU = understand commands, extract intent + entities. QA = answer questions from FAQ/documentation.'},
  {id:161,d:'d5',q:'Azure AI Speech STT vs OpenAI Whisper: when use which?',a:'Speech STT = real-time streaming, custom models, SSML, intent recognition. Whisper = batch transcription of audio files.'},
  {id:162,d:'d6',q:'Table projection vs Object projection vs File projection?',a:'Table = structured rows (Power BI). Object = full JSON docs (Blob). File = extracted images (Blob).'},
  {id:163,d:'d1',q:'Standard vs Global Standard vs Provisioned Throughput deployment?',a:'Standard = pay-per-token regional. Global Standard = multi-region routing. PTU = guaranteed reserved capacity.'},
  {id:164,d:'d5',q:'When to use each CLU entity type: Learned vs List vs Prebuilt vs Regex?',a:'Learned = context-dependent (ML). List = fixed values + synonyms. Prebuilt = common types (datetime). Regex = patterns (flight numbers).'},
  {id:165,d:'d4',q:'Image Analysis "people" feature vs Face API Detect?',a:'Image Analysis people = bounding boxes only (who is there count). Face API = identity, landmarks, attributes, recognition.'},
  {id:166,d:'d6',q:'fieldMappings vs outputFieldMappings: which for OCR output?',a:'outputFieldMappings — OCR is an enrichment output (after skillset), not source data.'},
  {id:167,d:'d5',q:'SpeechRecognizer vs IntentRecognizer vs TranslationRecognizer?',a:'SpeechRecognizer = just STT. IntentRecognizer = STT + CLU intent extraction. TranslationRecognizer = STT + translate to other languages.'},
  {id:168,d:'d4',q:'Video Indexer vs Spatial Analysis: when use which?',a:'Video Indexer = analyze recorded video (topics, transcript, faces). Spatial Analysis = real-time live camera (count people, zones).'},
];

const QUIZ_QUESTIONS = [
  {d:'d1',q:'You need to use Azure AI Language and Azure AI Vision with a single endpoint. What resource type?',
   opts:['Azure AI Language resource','Azure AI Vision resource','Azure AI Services multi-service resource','Two resources with a load balancer'],
   ans:2, exp:'Multi-service resource provides a single endpoint and key for multiple Azure AI services.'},
  {d:'d1',q:'API keys must be stored securely with rotation and no downtime. What should you use?',
   opts:['App settings','Azure Key Vault with managed identity','SAS tokens','Hardcode secondary key as backup'],
   ans:1, exp:'Key Vault + managed identity = secure storage with rotation, no credentials in code.'},
  {d:'d1',q:'You need to block the word "CompetitorName" from Azure OpenAI responses. What do you configure?',
   opts:['Content filters with high severity','A custom blocklist','Prompt shields','System message instruction'],
   ans:1, exp:'Blocklists block specific terms. Content filters work on categories (hate/sexual/violence/self-harm), not custom words.'},
  {d:'d1',q:'Which is NOT a Microsoft Responsible AI principle?',
   opts:['Fairness','Profitability','Transparency','Inclusiveness'],
   ans:1, exp:'The 6 principles are: Fairness, Reliability & Safety, Privacy & Security, Inclusiveness, Transparency, Accountability.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'You want highly creative marketing copy. Which parameter should you increase?',
   opts:['max_tokens','frequency_penalty','temperature','presence_penalty'],
   ans:2, exp:'Higher temperature (0.7-1.5) = more random/creative output.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'The model generates answers not found in provided documents. What should you implement?',
   opts:['Content filters','Groundedness detection','Prompt shields','Fine-tuning'],
   ans:1, exp:'Groundedness detection checks if the response is supported by the provided context.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'In a chat completion, which message role defines the assistant\'s behavior?',
   opts:['user','assistant','system','function'],
   ans:2, exp:'The system message sets behavior, persona, and constraints.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'You need guaranteed minimum tokens per minute. Which deployment type?',
   opts:['Standard','Global Standard','Provisioned Throughput','Data Zone Standard'],
   ans:2, exp:'Provisioned Throughput (PTU) reserves capacity with guaranteed tokens/min.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'You need bounding box coordinates for objects in an image. Which feature?',
   opts:['tags','caption','objects','people'],
   ans:2, exp:'The objects feature returns detected objects with bounding boxes.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'Images are blurry and small. Which Face detection model?',
   opts:['detection_01','detection_02','detection_03','recognition_04'],
   ans:1, exp:'detection_02 is optimized for small, side-view, and blurry faces. detection_03 also handles small faces well.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'You need face landmarks from blurry images. Which model?',
   opts:['detection_01','detection_02','detection_03','Any model'],
   ans:2, exp:'detection_02 handles blur but returns NO landmarks. detection_03 handles blur AND returns landmarks.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'Custom Vision model has high precision but low recall for "roses". What does this mean?',
   opts:['Misidentifies other flowers as roses','Rarely wrong when saying "rose" but misses many actual roses','Performs perfectly','Too many rose images in training'],
   ans:1, exp:'High precision = few false positives. Low recall = many false negatives (misses real roses).'},
  {d:'d5',q:'Detect if a review is positive, negative, or neutral. Which feature?',
   opts:['Key phrase extraction','Entity recognition','Sentiment analysis','Language detection'],
   ans:2, exp:'Sentiment analysis returns positive, negative, neutral, or mixed.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'"Book me a flight to Paris tomorrow." What is the intent and what are entities?',
   opts:['Intent: Paris, Entities: Book, tomorrow','Intent: BookFlight, Entities: Paris (dest), tomorrow (date)','Intent: tomorrow, Entities: Paris, flight','Intent: travel, Entities: BookFlight'],
   ans:1, exp:'BookFlight is the intent (action). Paris and tomorrow are entities (parameters).'},
  {d:'d5',q:'You want TTS with slower pace and higher pitch. What SSML tag?',
   opts:['<voice>','<prosody rate="slow" pitch="+10%">','<break>','<emphasis>'],
   ans:1, exp:'<prosody> controls rate, pitch, and volume of synthesized speech.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'You need to detect and redact SSNs and emails from text. Which feature?',
   opts:['Entity recognition','PII detection','Key phrase extraction','Sentiment analysis'],
   ans:1, exp:'PII detection identifies personal data and provides redactedText.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'Your FAQ bot should ask follow-up clarification questions. What feature?',
   opts:['Chit-chat','Alternate phrasing','Multi-turn conversation','Active learning'],
   ans:2, exp:'Multi-turn conversations enable follow-up prompts for clarification.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Enrich documents with AI key phrases during indexing. What to configure?',
   opts:['A data source','An indexer','A skillset','A synonym map'],
   ans:2, exp:'A skillset defines the AI enrichment pipeline applied during indexing.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Custom AI enrichment calling your own API. What to create?',
   opts:['Built-in skill','Custom skill (Azure Function)','Knowledge store projection','Scoring profile'],
   ans:1, exp:'Custom skills are Azure Functions with the Web API skill type.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Return only hotels rated 4+, sorted by price. Which query parameters?',
   opts:['$filter=rating ge 4&$orderby=price asc','search=rating:4&sort=price','$select=rating,price&$top=4','queryType=full&search=rating:[4 TO *]'],
   ans:0, exp:'$filter for conditions, $orderby for sorting — OData query syntax.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Invoices from various vendors with different layouts. Which approach?',
   opts:['Prebuilt Invoice model','Custom template model','Custom neural model','Build from scratch'],
   ans:0, exp:'The prebuilt-invoice model handles varying invoice layouts out of the box.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Three custom models, one endpoint, auto-routing. What to create?',
   opts:['Custom skill','Composed model','Prebuilt model','An indexer'],
   ans:1, exp:'A composed model combines custom models and routes automatically.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Store enriched data in Azure Table Storage for Power BI. What to configure?',
   opts:['An index','A data source','Knowledge store with table projections','A custom skill'],
   ans:2, exp:'Knowledge store table projections save enriched data to Azure Table Storage.'},
  {d:'d3',q:'Build an AI agent that searches web, queries DB, generates reports. Which service?',
   opts:['Azure AI Language','Microsoft Foundry Agent Service','Azure AI Search','Azure Logic Apps'],
   ans:1, exp:'Foundry Agent Service builds autonomous agents with tool use.'},
  {d:'d3',q:'In the Agent API, what object do you create to trigger the agent to process a conversation?',
   opts:['Agent','Thread','Message','Run'],
   ans:3, exp:'A Run executes the agent on a thread. Thread holds messages, Run triggers processing.'},
  // Additional quiz questions
  {d:'d1',q:'Your company requires Azure AI services in an isolated network. What should you deploy?',
   opts:['VNet with service endpoints only','Azure AI in a Docker container','Private endpoint for the resource','Both container and private endpoint are valid'],
   ans:3, exp:'Both containers (disconnected) and private endpoints (network-isolated) work for isolation.'},
  {d:'d1',q:'You are regenerating API keys. The app currently uses Key 1. Which key should you regenerate FIRST?',
   opts:['Key 1','Key 2','Both simultaneously','Neither — use managed identity instead'],
   ans:1, exp:'Regenerate Key 2 first (app doesn\'t use it), then switch app to Key 2, then regenerate Key 1.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'The model keeps repeating the same paragraph. Which parameter should you increase?',
   opts:['temperature','frequency_penalty','presence_penalty','max_tokens'],
   ans:1, exp:'frequency_penalty penalizes tokens based on how often they appeared. presence_penalty is for encouraging new topics.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'You want to provide few-shot examples in a chat completion. Which message role do you use for the example responses?',
   opts:['system','user','assistant','function'],
   ans:2, exp:'Few-shot examples use alternating user/assistant message pairs. The assistant role carries the example responses.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'What is the minimum fine-tuning data required?',
   opts:['5 examples','10 examples','50 examples','100 examples'],
   ans:1, exp:'Minimum is 10 examples, but 50-100+ is recommended for quality.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'Which Face detection model supports the mask attribute?',
   opts:['detection_01','detection_02','detection_03','All detection models'],
   ans:2, exp:'The mask attribute is only available with detection_03.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'You need to identify WHO a person is from a photo. Which service?',
   opts:['Image Analysis 4.0 (people feature)','Face API (Identify)','Custom Vision','Video Indexer'],
   ans:1, exp:'Image Analysis detects people with bounding boxes but NOT identity. Face API Identify matches against a PersonGroup.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'You created a PersonGroup with recognition_03. Can you add faces detected with recognition_04?',
   opts:['Yes, models are interchangeable','No, recognition models must match','Yes, but only for Verify operations','Yes, if you retrain the group'],
   ans:1, exp:'A PersonGroup always uses the recognition model it was created with. Models must be consistent.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'Language detection returns "unknown" with what confidence score?',
   opts:['0.0','0.5','1.0','NaN'],
   ans:2, exp:'Ambiguous content returns "unknown" with confidence 1.0 (not 0.0!). The iso code is NaN.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'Which SDK class do you use for keyword/wake word detection?',
   opts:['SpeechRecognizer','IntentRecognizer','KeywordRecognizer','TranslationRecognizer'],
   ans:2, exp:'KeywordRecognizer detects wake words with a keyword model (.table file).'},
  {d:'d5',q:'CLU: which entity type uses a fixed list of values with synonyms?',
   opts:['Learned','List','Prebuilt','Regex'],
   ans:1, exp:'List entities define fixed values with synonyms. Learned uses ML from labeled examples.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'You need to add a suggester to existing fields in an index. What happens?',
   opts:['It works immediately','You must rebuild the index','Just rerun the indexer','Update the skillset'],
   ans:1, exp:'Adding a suggester to existing fields requires an index rebuild because prefixes must be re-indexed.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Map the OCR enrichment output to an index field. Which mapping type?',
   opts:['fieldMappings','outputFieldMappings','skillset inputs','index projections'],
   ans:1, exp:'outputFieldMappings maps enrichment outputs (after skillset) to index fields. fieldMappings is for source data before enrichment.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Which scoring function interpolation types are NOT allowed for the tag function?',
   opts:['linear and constant','quadratic and logarithmic','constant and logarithmic','All are allowed'],
   ans:1, exp:'Quadratic and logarithmic interpolation are not allowed for tag scoring functions.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'What is the @odata.type for the OCR built-in skill?',
   opts:['#Microsoft.Skills.Text.OcrSkill','#Microsoft.Skills.Vision.OcrSkill','#Microsoft.Skills.Custom.OcrSkill','#Microsoft.Skills.Util.OcrSkill'],
   ans:1, exp:'OCR is a Vision skill: #Microsoft.Skills.Vision.OcrSkill'},
  {d:'d1',q:'What Azure OpenAI deployment type routes traffic globally for highest availability?',
   opts:['Standard','Global Standard','Provisioned Throughput','Data Zone Standard'],
   ans:1, exp:'Global Standard provides multi-region routing for highest availability. Standard is regional.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'In Microsoft Foundry, what measures whether an AI response is supported by provided context?',
   opts:['Relevance','Coherence','Groundedness','Fluency'],
   ans:2, exp:'Groundedness checks if the answer is supported by the context. Relevance checks if it addresses the question.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'You need speech-to-speech translation (spoken English → spoken French). What extra config is needed?',
   opts:['Add target language only','Add voice_name for target language','Use SpeechSynthesizer separately','Use custom speech model'],
   ans:1, exp:'Speech-to-text translation just needs add_target_language. Speech-to-speech also needs a voice_name for synthesized output.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'What QualityForRecognition level is recommended for person identification?',
   opts:['Low or better','Medium or better','High only','Any quality'],
   ans:1, exp:'Medium or better for identification. High is recommended for enrollment.'},
  // SSML questions
  {d:'d5',q:'Which SSML tag adds a 500ms pause between sentences?',
   opts:['<prosody time="500ms">','<break time="500ms"/>','<pause duration="500ms"/>','<silence length="500ms"/>'],
   ans:1, exp:'<break time="500ms"/> inserts a pause. <prosody> controls rate/pitch/volume, not pauses.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'You need TTS to read "12/25/2024" as a date rather than a math expression. Which SSML tag?',
   opts:['<prosody interpret-as="date">','<say-as interpret-as="date" format="mdy">','<format type="date">','<voice style="date">'],
   ans:1, exp:'<say-as interpret-as="date" format="mdy"> tells the synthesizer to read it as month/day/year.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'SSML: the <mstts:express-as> tag requires what namespace declaration?',
   opts:['xmlns:mstts="http://www.w3.org/2001/mstts"','xmlns:mstts="http://schemas.microsoft.com/speech"','No namespace needed','xmlns:ssml="http://www.w3.org/2001/10/synthesis"'],
   ans:0, exp:'The mstts namespace must be declared: xmlns:mstts="http://www.w3.org/2001/mstts". Without it, the SSML is invalid.'},
  // Container/edge questions
  {d:'d1',q:'You deploy an Azure AI container on-premises. It stops working after 24 hours. Why?',
   opts:['Container license expired','Container lost billing connection (phone-home)','Container needs GPU','Container image is too old'],
   ans:1, exp:'Azure AI containers require periodic billing connections. Without it, they stop after the grace period. Disconnected containers need special approval.'},
  {d:'d1',q:'Where does Spatial Analysis run?',
   opts:['Azure cloud only','Any Docker host','Edge device with NVIDIA GPU','Azure Kubernetes Service only'],
   ans:2, exp:'Spatial Analysis runs as a Docker container on edge devices with NVIDIA GPU, processing RTSP video streams.'},
  // Video Indexer / Spatial Analysis
  {d:'d4',q:'You need to extract topics, keywords, and detect scenes from a corporate training video. Which service?',
   opts:['Azure AI Vision - Image Analysis','Azure AI Video Indexer','Azure AI Vision - Spatial Analysis','Azure Media Services'],
   ans:1, exp:'Video Indexer extracts topics, keywords, transcript, scenes, faces, and more from video. Spatial Analysis is for real-time people detection.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'You need to count how many people enter a retail store zone from a security camera feed. Which service?',
   opts:['Azure AI Video Indexer','Azure AI Vision - Image Analysis','Azure AI Vision - Spatial Analysis','Custom Vision'],
   ans:2, exp:'Spatial Analysis processes live video (RTSP) to count people, detect zone crossings, and measure dwell time. Video Indexer is for recorded video analysis.'},
  // More D3 (agentic)
  {d:'d3',q:'In Semantic Kernel, what is a collection of callable functions that an agent can use?',
   opts:['Kernel','Plugin','Planner','Connector'],
   ans:1, exp:'A Plugin is a collection of functions. The Kernel orchestrates them. The Planner auto-creates execution plans.'},
  {d:'d3',q:'A manager agent delegates subtasks to specialized worker agents. What pattern is this?',
   opts:['Sequential','Parallel','Hierarchical','Collaborative'],
   ans:2, exp:'Hierarchical: a manager agent delegates to worker agents. Sequential chains agents in order. Collaborative has agents discuss together.'},
  // Field attribute scenario questions
  {d:'d6',q:'Your search UI needs a sidebar showing count of results per category (e.g., "Hotels: 42"). What field attribute do you need on the category field?',
   opts:['searchable','filterable','facetable','sortable'],
   ans:2, exp:'Facetable enables faceted navigation — count-by-category sidebars. Filterable is for $filter conditions, not category counts.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'A field contains internal scoring data. It should be used in $filter but NOT shown in search results. What attributes?',
   opts:['filterable=true, retrievable=true','filterable=true, retrievable=false','searchable=true, retrievable=false','sortable=true, filterable=false'],
   ans:1, exp:'filterable=true allows $filter usage. retrievable=false hides it from API results. searchable is for free-text search, not filtering.'},
  // Decision scenario quiz questions
  {d:'d2',q:'Your AI generates good answers but sometimes makes up facts not in the provided documents. What should you try FIRST?',
   opts:['Fine-tune the model','Implement RAG with Azure AI Search','Increase temperature','Add more stop sequences'],
   ans:1, exp:'RAG grounds the model in actual documents. Fine-tuning teaches style, not factual accuracy. Temperature affects creativity, not factuality.'},
  {d:'d2',q:'You need the model to always respond in a specific JSON schema with domain-specific terminology. Prompt engineering alone isn\'t working. What next?',
   opts:['RAG','Fine-tuning','Increase max_tokens','Change to a larger model'],
   ans:1, exp:'Fine-tuning teaches format/style/domain behavior. RAG is for grounding in data, not for output format control.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'Your search must support queries like "hotel~2" (fuzzy) and "title:luxury" (field-scoped). What must you set?',
   opts:['searchMode=all','queryType=full','semanticConfiguration=default','$filter=queryType eq full'],
   ans:1, exp:'Fuzzy search (~) and field-scoped search (field:value) require Full Lucene syntax: queryType=full.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'You want search results re-ranked by deep learning for better relevance, with auto-generated captions. What do you configure?',
   opts:['Vector search with HNSW','Semantic search with a semantic configuration','A scoring profile with freshness function','Full Lucene with term boosting'],
   ans:1, exp:'Semantic search re-ranks with deep learning models and provides captions + answers. Vector search uses embeddings. Scoring profiles use numeric functions.'},
  {d:'d1',q:'You need Azure AI services to run in a factory with no internet connection. What do you need?',
   opts:['Standard cloud deployment with VPN','Connected container','Disconnected container (requires approval)','Private endpoint'],
   ans:2, exp:'Disconnected containers run fully offline but require special Microsoft approval. Connected containers still need internet for billing.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'You have forms with identical fixed layouts (same positions every time). Which Doc Intelligence model type?',
   opts:['Prebuilt','Custom template','Custom neural','Composed'],
   ans:1, exp:'Template models are for fixed-layout forms where fields are always in the same position. Neural is for variable layouts.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'User says "Book a flight to Paris" — you need to extract the action and destination. Which service?',
   opts:['Custom Question Answering','Text Analytics (entities)','CLU (intents + entities)','Azure Translator'],
   ans:2, exp:'CLU extracts intent (BookFlight) and entities (destination=Paris). QA returns FAQ answers. Text Analytics finds generic named entities but not custom intents.'},
  {d:'d5',q:'You need real-time speech recognition with custom vocabulary for medical terms. Which service?',
   opts:['Azure OpenAI Whisper','Azure AI Speech with Custom Speech model','Azure AI Language','Azure Translator'],
   ans:1, exp:'Azure AI Speech supports custom STT models trained on your audio + transcripts for domain-specific vocabulary. Whisper is batch-only with no custom models.'},
  {d:'d4',q:'Your app needs to detect faces in blurry surveillance footage AND return face landmarks. Which detection model?',
   opts:['detection_01','detection_02','detection_03','recognition_04'],
   ans:2, exp:'detection_03 handles blurry/small faces AND returns landmarks. detection_02 handles blur but returns NO landmarks. recognition_04 is a recognition model, not detection.'},
  {d:'d6',q:'You want to store enriched key phrases in Azure Table Storage for Power BI analysis. What do you configure?',
   opts:['An output field mapping to a table','A knowledge store with table projections','A custom skill writing to Table Storage','A scoring profile'],
   ans:1, exp:'Knowledge store table projections write structured data to Azure Table Storage. Output field mappings go to the search index, not external storage.'},
];

// ==================== CHEAT SHEET DATA ====================
const CHEATSHEETS = [
  {d:'d1', title:'Service Selection Matrix', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Need</th><th>Service</th></tr>
<tr><td>Chat, text gen, code</td><td><b>Azure OpenAI</b> (GPT-4o)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Image generation</td><td><b>Azure OpenAI</b> (gpt-image-1)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Image analysis (tags, objects)</td><td><b>Azure AI Vision</b> (Image Analysis 4.0)</td></tr>
<tr><td>OCR</td><td><b>Azure AI Vision</b> (Read API)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Face detection/recognition</td><td><b>Azure AI Face</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Custom image classify/detect</td><td><b>Custom Vision</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Video analysis</td><td><b>Azure AI Video Indexer</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Sentiment, entities, PII</td><td><b>Azure AI Language</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Text translation</td><td><b>Azure AI Translator</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Speech-to-text / TTS</td><td><b>Azure AI Speech</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Search + AI enrichment</td><td><b>Azure AI Search</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Invoice/receipt extraction</td><td><b>Document Intelligence</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Content moderation</td><td><b>Azure AI Content Safety</b></td></tr>
<tr><td>AI agents</td><td><b>Foundry Agent Service</b></td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d1', title:'Authentication Methods', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Method</th><th>Header / Code</th><th>When</th></tr>
<tr><td>Subscription key</td><td><code>Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key</code></td><td>Dev/test</td></tr>
<tr><td>Entra ID token</td><td><code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code></td><td>Production (RBAC)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Managed Identity</td><td><code>DefaultAzureCredential()</code></td><td>No creds in code</td></tr>
<tr><td>Key Vault</td><td>Store + rotate keys</td><td>Secure storage</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Translator trap:</b> Uses global endpoint <code>api.cognitive.microsofttranslator.com</code> + requires <code>Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Region</code> header.</p>`},
  {d:'d1', title:'Responsible AI — Content Safety', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Feature</th><th>What</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Content filter</b></td><td>Blocks by category (hate/sexual/violence/self-harm) at severity levels</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Blocklist</b></td><td>Blocks specific terms YOU define</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Prompt shields</b></td><td>Detects prompt injection / jailbreak</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Groundedness</b></td><td>Checks response is supported by context</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Protected material</b></td><td>Detects copyrighted content</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d2', title:'OpenAI Parameters', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Param</th><th>Controls</th><th>Range</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>temperature</code></td><td>Randomness</td><td>0.0–2.0</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>top_p</code></td><td>Nucleus sampling</td><td>0.0–1.0</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>max_tokens</code></td><td>Output length</td><td>1 – model max</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>frequency_penalty</code></td><td>Reduce repetition</td><td>-2.0–2.0</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>presence_penalty</code></td><td>Encourage new topics</td><td>-2.0–2.0</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>stop</code></td><td>Stop sequences</td><td>Up to 4</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Rule:</b> Don't set both temperature AND top_p — pick one.</p>`},
  {d:'d2', title:'RAG Pattern', content:`<p><code>User query → Azure AI Search (retrieves docs) → Docs injected as context → Azure OpenAI generates grounded answer</code></p>
<table class="cs-table" style="margin-top:12px"><tr><th>Component</th><th>Service</th></tr>
<tr><td>Embeddings</td><td>text-embedding-3-small/large</td></tr>
<tr><td>Vector/Semantic search</td><td>Azure AI Search</td></tr>
<tr><td>Generation</td><td>Azure OpenAI (GPT-4o)</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d4', title:'Face API Models — MEMORIZE', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Model</th><th>Best For</th><th>Landmarks?</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>detection_01</code></td><td>General (default)</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>detection_02</code></td><td><b>Blurry, small, side-view</b></td><td><b>No</b></td></tr>
<tr><td><code>detection_03</code></td><td><b>Best overall</b></td><td>Yes</td></tr></table>
<table class="cs-table" style="margin-top:12px"><tr><th>Model</th><th>Best For</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>recognition_04</code></td><td><b>Best accuracy + face masks</b></td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Rules:</b> Can't change model after PersonGroup creation. detection_02 = NO landmarks, NO attributes. Default = detection_01 + recognition_01.</p>`},
  {d:'d5', title:'SSML Tags', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Tag</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;speak&gt;</code></td><td>Root element</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;voice&gt;</code></td><td>Select voice</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;prosody&gt;</code></td><td>Rate, pitch, volume</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;break&gt;</code></td><td>Pause</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;emphasis&gt;</code></td><td>Emphasize word</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;say-as&gt;</code></td><td>Pronunciation (date, phone, cardinal)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>&lt;mstts:express-as&gt;</code></td><td>Emotional style (cheerful, sad)</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d5', title:'CLU Concepts', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Concept</th><th>Example</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Intent</b></td><td>BookFlight, GetWeather</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Entity</b></td><td>destination=Paris, date=tomorrow</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Utterance</b></td><td>"Book me a flight to Paris"</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>None intent</b></td><td>Always include — catches out-of-scope</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Entity types:</b> Learned, List, Prebuilt, Regex</p>`},
  {d:'d6', title:'Search Architecture', content:`<p><code>Data Source → Indexer → [Skillset] → Index → Queries</code></p>
<table class="cs-table" style="margin-top:12px"><tr><th>Mapping</th><th>When</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>fieldMappings</code></td><td>Before enrichment (source → index)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>outputFieldMappings</code></td><td>After enrichment (skillset → index)</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d6', title:'Search Query Syntax', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Param</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>$filter</code></td><td>Exact match / comparison</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>$orderby</code></td><td>Sort results</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>$select</code></td><td>Choose returned fields</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>$top / $skip</code></td><td>Pagination</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>queryType=full</code></td><td>Enable Lucene (fuzzy, wildcard, regex)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>searchMode=all</code></td><td>All terms must match (AND)</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Operators:</b> eq, ne, gt, ge, lt, le, and, or, not, search.in(), geo.distance(), any(), all()</p>`},
  {d:'d6', title:'Document Intelligence Models', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Model ID</th><th>Extracts</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-invoice</code></td><td>Vendor, dates, line items</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-receipt</code></td><td>Merchant, items, total</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-idDocument</code></td><td>Name, DOB, doc number</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-read</code></td><td>OCR text extraction</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-layout</code></td><td>Tables + structure</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-tax.us.w2</code></td><td>W-2 tax form fields</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-businessCard</code></td><td>Name, company, phone, email</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>prebuilt-document</code></td><td>Key-value pairs, entities, tables</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Custom:</b> Template (fixed layout) vs Neural (variable). Min 5 labeled docs. <b>Composed</b> = combine + auto-route (max 200 components).</p>`},
  // NEW cheat sheet sections
  {d:'d1', title:'Deployment Types', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Type</th><th>Key Feature</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Standard</b></td><td>Pay-per-token, shared infrastructure</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Global Standard</b></td><td>Multi-region routing, highest availability</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Provisioned Throughput (PTU)</b></td><td>Reserved capacity, guaranteed tokens/min</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Data Zone Standard</b></td><td>Data stays in specified geography</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Exam tip:</b> "Guaranteed minimum tokens per minute" = Provisioned Throughput</p>`},
  {d:'d1', title:'RBAC Roles', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Role</th><th>Permissions</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>Cognitive Services User</code></td><td>Call APIs (read only)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>Cognitive Services Contributor</code></td><td>Manage resources + call APIs</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>Cognitive Services OpenAI User</code></td><td>Call OpenAI APIs specifically</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>Cognitive Services OpenAI Contributor</code></td><td>Manage OpenAI deployments + call APIs</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d1', title:'Networking & Containers', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Private Endpoint</b></td><td>Private IP within your VNet; no public internet</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Service Endpoint</b></td><td>Optimized route from VNet (still public IP)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Firewall rules</b></td><td>Allow specific IP ranges</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Containers:</b> Docker images from <code>mcr.microsoft.com/azure-cognitive-services/</code>. Require billing phone-home unless <b>disconnected container</b> (special approval).</p>`},
  {d:'d1', title:'Monitoring & Key Metrics', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>Azure Monitor</td><td>Metrics, logs, alerts</td></tr>
<tr><td>Diagnostic settings</td><td>Route to Log Analytics, Storage, Event Hubs</td></tr>
<tr><td>Application Insights</td><td>End-to-end tracing</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cost Management</td><td>Budgets, alerts, spending analysis</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Metrics:</b> Total Calls, Total Errors, Latency, Blocked Calls (429). <b>Tiers:</b> Free (F0) vs Standard (S0).</p>`},
  {d:'d1', title:'REST API Endpoint Patterns', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Service</th><th>Pattern</th></tr>
<tr><td>Multi-service</td><td><code>&lt;resource&gt;.cognitiveservices.azure.com/</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Azure OpenAI</td><td><code>&lt;resource&gt;.openai.azure.com/openai/deployments/&lt;deployment&gt;/...</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>AI Search</td><td><code>&lt;service&gt;.search.windows.net/</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Translator</td><td><code>api.cognitive.microsofttranslator.com/</code> (GLOBAL)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Speech</td><td><code>&lt;region&gt;.api.cognitive.microsoft.com/</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Face API</td><td><code>&lt;resource&gt;.cognitiveservices.azure.com/face/v1.0/detect</code></td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d2', title:'OpenAI Models', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Model</th><th>Best For</th><th>Context</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>GPT-4o</b></td><td>Multimodal, fastest GPT-4 class</td><td>128K in / 16K out</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>GPT-4o-mini</b></td><td>Fast, cheap (replaces GPT-3.5)</td><td>128K in / 16K out</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>GPT-4 Turbo</b></td><td>Complex reasoning + vision</td><td>128K in / 4K out</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>gpt-image-1</b></td><td>Image generation</td><td>N/A</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Whisper</b></td><td>Audio transcription</td><td>25 MB file</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>text-embedding-3-large</b></td><td>Best embeddings (3,072 dims)</td><td>8K tokens</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>text-embedding-3-small</b></td><td>Cheaper embeddings (1,536 dims)</td><td>8K tokens</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d2', title:'Prompt Engineering', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Technique</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Zero-shot</b></td><td>No examples, just instruction</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Few-shot</b></td><td>Provide examples in the prompt (user/assistant pairs)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Chain-of-thought</b></td><td>"Think step by step"</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Grounding</b></td><td>Provide reference docs as context (RAG)</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Best practices:</b> Use delimiters (\`\`\`, """). Specify output format. Use system message for rules. Be specific.</p>`},
  {d:'d2', title:'Foundry — Hub, Project, Prompt Flow', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Concept</th><th>What</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Hub</b></td><td>Top-level resource: shared compute, connections, policies</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Project</b></td><td>Workspace within a hub (per team/use case)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Connections</b></td><td>Links to OpenAI, AI Search, storage</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Prompt flow</b></td><td>Visual LLM orchestration (nodes: LLM, Python, Prompt, Tool)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Evaluation</b></td><td>Groundedness, Relevance, Coherence, Fluency, Similarity</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Tracing</b></td><td>Debug request pipeline</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d2', title:'Fine-Tuning & Image Generation', content:`<p><b>Fine-tuning:</b> JSONL format, min 10 examples, models: GPT-4o, GPT-4o-mini, GPT-4.1 series. Result = new deployment. Cost = training + hosting.</p>
<p style="margin-top:8px"><b>RAG vs Fine-tune:</b> RAG = dynamic data grounding. Fine-tune = style/format/domain behavior.</p>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Image gen (DALL-E / gpt-image-1):</b></p>
<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Size</th><th>Aspect</th></tr>
<tr><td>1024×1024</td><td>Square</td></tr>
<tr><td>1792×1024</td><td>Landscape</td></tr>
<tr><td>1024×1792</td><td>Portrait</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:8px">Quality: <code>standard</code> (fast) or <code>hd</code> (detailed)</p>`},
  {d:'d3', title:'Agent Service — API Objects & Flow', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Object</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Agent</b></td><td>Definition: model, instructions, tools</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Thread</b></td><td>Conversation container</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Message</b></td><td>Single message (user or assistant)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Run</b></td><td>Execution of agent on a thread</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>RunStep</b></td><td>Individual step (tool call, message)</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Flow:</b> Create Agent → Create Thread → Add Messages → Create Run → Poll results</p>
<p style="margin-top:8px"><b>Tools:</b> Code Interpreter, File Search, Function Calling, Azure AI Search, Bing, Azure Functions</p>`},
  {d:'d3', title:'Semantic Kernel & Multi-Agent', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Concept</th><th>What</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Kernel</b></td><td>Central orchestrator</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Plugin</b></td><td>Collection of callable functions</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Planner</b></td><td>Auto-creates plans from functions</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Memory</b></td><td>Stores conversation history</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Multi-agent patterns:</b> Sequential (chain), Parallel (simultaneous), Hierarchical (manager→workers), Collaborative (discuss + refine)</p>`},
  {d:'d4', title:'Custom Vision', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Type</th><th>Task</th><th>Min Images/Tag</th></tr>
<tr><td>Classification</td><td>What is it?</td><td>5 (30+ rec)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Object Detection</td><td>Where is it?</td><td>15 (50+ rec)</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Metrics:</b> Precision (false positive rate), Recall (false negative rate), AP (area under PR curve), mAP (mean across classes)</p>
<p style="margin-top:8px"><b>Domains:</b> General, General (compact/exportable), Food, Landmarks, Retail</p>
<p style="margin-top:8px"><b>Compact models</b> export to ONNX/TensorFlow/CoreML for edge.</p>
<p style="margin-top:8px"><b>⚠️ Retiring Sept 2028</b> — migrate to Azure ML AutoML or Content Understanding</p>`},
  {d:'d4', title:'Video Indexer & Spatial Analysis', content:`<p><b>Video Indexer extracts:</b> Faces, OCR, topics, keywords, sentiment, scenes, shots, transcript, translation, labels, brands, named entities</p>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Spatial Analysis operations:</b></p>
<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Operation</th><th>Detects</th></tr>
<tr><td>Person counting</td><td>Count people in a zone</td></tr>
<tr><td>Person distance</td><td>Distance between people</td></tr>
<tr><td>Zone crossing</td><td>Enter/exit a zone</td></tr>
<tr><td>Line crossing</td><td>Cross a virtual line</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dwell time</td><td>How long in a zone</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Requires:</b> Edge device, Docker container, NVIDIA GPU, RTSP video stream</p>`},
  {d:'d4', title:'Face API Parameters & Attributes', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>detectionModel</code></td><td>detection_01, _02, _03</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>recognitionModel</code></td><td>recognition_01 – _04</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>returnFaceId</code></td><td>Must be true for recognition</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>returnFaceLandmarks</code></td><td>27 facial landmark points</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>returnFaceAttributes</code></td><td>blur, exposure, glasses, headPose, mask, noise, occlusion, qualityForRecognition</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>faceIdTimeToLive</code></td><td>Default: 86400s (24h)</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Limits:</b> Min face: 36×36px. Max face: 4096×4096px. Max image: 6 MB. Formats: JPEG, PNG, GIF (1st frame), BMP.</p>
<p style="margin-top:8px"><b>Quality:</b> High for enrollment, Medium+ for identification. Only with detection_01/03 + recognition_03/04.</p>`},
  {d:'d5', title:'Text Analytics Endpoints', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Path</th></tr>
<tr><td>Sentiment</td><td><code>/text/analytics/v3.1/sentiment</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Key Phrases</td><td><code>/text/analytics/v3.1/keyPhrases</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Entities</td><td><code>/text/analytics/v3.1/entities/recognition/general</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>PII</td><td><code>/text/analytics/v3.1/entities/recognition/pii</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Language</td><td><code>/text/analytics/v3.1/languages</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Entity Linking</td><td><code>/text/analytics/v3.1/entities/linking</code></td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Limits:</b> Max 1,000 docs/request. Max 5,120 chars/doc. Max 1 MB/request. Language detection doesn't need <code>language</code> field.</p>`},
  {d:'d5', title:'Speech SDK Classes', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Task</th><th>Class</th></tr>
<tr><td>Speech-to-text</td><td><code>SpeechRecognizer</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Text-to-speech</td><td><code>SpeechSynthesizer</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Speech + intent</td><td><code>IntentRecognizer</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Speech translation</td><td><code>TranslationRecognizer</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Keyword/wake word</td><td><code>KeywordRecognizer</code></td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Config classes:</b> <code>SpeechConfig</code> (STT/TTS), <code>SpeechTranslationConfig</code> (translation). Set <code>speech_recognition_language</code>, <code>speech_synthesis_voice_name</code>.</p>`},
  {d:'d5', title:'Translator & Question Answering', content:`<p><b>Translator:</b> Global endpoint <code>api.cognitive.microsofttranslator.com</code>. Requires <code>Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Region</code> header.</p>
<table class="cs-table" style="margin-top:8px"><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
<tr><td>Multi-target</td><td><code>to=fr&to=de&to=ja</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Transliterate</td><td>Script conversion (not translation)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Custom Translator</td><td>10,000+ parallel sentences needed</td></tr></table>
<p style="margin-top:12px"><b>Custom Question Answering:</b></p>
<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>Multi-turn</td><td>Follow-up prompts</td></tr>
<tr><td>Alternate phrasing</td><td>Multiple questions → same answer</td></tr>
<tr><td>Chit-chat</td><td>Professional, Friendly, Witty, Caring, Enthusiastic</td></tr>
<tr><td>Active learning</td><td>Suggests questions from traffic</td></tr>
<tr><td>Precise answering</td><td>Short answer from longer passage</td></tr></table>`},
  {d:'d6', title:'Built-in Skills (@odata.type)', content:`<table class="cs-table"><tr><th>Skill</th><th>@odata.type</th></tr>
<tr><td>OCR</td><td><code>#Microsoft.Skills.Vision.OcrSkill</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Image Analysis</td><td><code>#Microsoft.Skills.Vision.ImageAnalysisSkill</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Key Phrases</td><td><code>#Microsoft.Skills.Text.KeyPhraseExtractionSkill</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Entities</td><td><code>#Microsoft.Skills.Text.V3.EntityRecognitionSkill</code></td></tr>
